.TH "CAPNG_STAGE_SUPPLEMENTARY_GROUPS" "3" "Mar 2026" "Red Hat" \
"Libcap-ng API"
.SH NAME
capng_stage_supplementary_groups \- stage supplementary gids for
capng_change_id
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.B #include <cap-ng.h>
.sp
int capng_stage_supplementary_groups(const gid_t *gids, size_t count);

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This function stages a supplementary gid list for the next
.BR capng_change_id (3)
call that uses
.BR CAPNG_APPLY_STAGED_SUPP_GRP .
The gids are copied into libcap-ng internal state.

This interface is available in libcap-ng 0.9.3 and later. Applications
that also support older releases should check for the new symbol before
using it.

The staged list is one-shot state. Once
.B capng_change_id
returns, libcap-ng clears the staged gids whether they were applied,
ignored because the flag was not set, or discarded because the call
failed. If staged gids remain unused, libcap-ng also clears them when the
thread-local state is deinitialized.

Passing a
.I count
of 0 clears any currently staged gids.

.SH "RETURN VALUE"

This returns 0 on success and -1 on failure. A non-zero
.I count
with a NULL
.I gids
pointer fails with
.B errno
set to
.BR EINVAL .

.SH "SEE ALSO"

.BR capng_change_id (3),
.BR capabilities (7)

.SH AUTHOR
Steve Grubb
